public void setItems(@NonNull

        Description copied from interface: AutoCompleteTypeAdapter
        Set a list of items for this type adapter. Note that the list will be processed and indexed asynchronously, and used for the next filtering.

        This method can be called to replace an existing data set, even after the MultiAutoComplete has been created. The data set change will be notified and the filter updated accordingly.

      • setOnTokensChangedListener

        public final void setOnTokensChangedListener(@Nullable
                                             OnTokensChangedListener<M> listener)
        Description copied from interface: AutoCompleteTypeAdapter
        Set a OnTokensChangedListener to listen for changes in the matched tokens in the user-typed text.

        Note: this method can only be called if the token filter returned by TokenFilter.getValidTokenPattern() is not null, since it's required to detect the token matches within the user typed string.
